ndian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"la","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Cuong, Anh, Thanh, Ha, Hoang, Tuan, Chau, Hao, Hien, Hoa, Hue, Nam, Phong, Sinh, Tuong, Min, Tam, Tanh, Thai, Tham, Tinh, Yeong.  Chinese Hong, Hang, Sang, Tong, Chan, Chi, Hwa Ja, Hyung, Kam, Ki Bong, Kin, Man.","Vietnamese: from the Chinese surname 羅, see   Luo   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Lã</b>): from the Chinese surname 呂, see   Lu   6 and 3 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Luo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Jian, Yi, Ping, Yong, Zhen, Feng, Hong, Ming, Jin, Bin, Chen, Hai, Lan, Min, Huan, Hung, Shen, Tian.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 羅, meaning ‘net for catching birds’ or ‘to collect’ in Chinese: (i) from Luo (羅), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Hubei province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu during the early Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), people from the state migrated southwards and adopted Luo (羅) as their surname. (ii) from the Po Duo Luo (破多羅) and Chi Luo (叱羅) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their original surnames to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) from the personal name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅), leader of an ancient Turkic tribe who are believed to have migrated to China during the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ). His descendants inherited his name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅) as their surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Rivière","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Camille, Firmin, Hermite, Lucien, Monique, Stephane.","French (<b>Rivière</b>): topographic name for someone who lived by the bank of a river or shore of a lake, from Old French <i>riviere</i> ‘river, shore’ (originally meaning ‘riverbank’, from Latin <i>riparia</i>); or a habitational name from any of various places called (La) Rivière, for example in Indre-et-Loire and Pas-de-Calais. Compare   Lariviere   1 and 2.","History: Joseph Rivière from Bordeaux in Gironde, France, married Félicité Audet in Carleton, QC, in 1795."],"variants":[{"name":"Rivoire","meanings":["French: topographic name, a regional variant of <b>Rivière</b> (see   Riviere  ), or a habitational name from (La) Rivoire, the name of several places mainly in the southeastern part of France. Compare   Revere  .","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its altered form <i>Revere</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Reviere","meanings":["Altered form of French   Riviere   and possibly also of Dutch   Revier  .","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."]},{"name":"Lariviere","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Normand, Fernand, Marcel, Adelard, Andre, Gaston, Philibert, Aime, Alcide, Alphonse, Antoine.","French (<b>Larivière</b>):","habitational name from any of numerous places in various parts of France named Larivière or La Rivière, from Old French <i>riviere</i> ‘river, shore’."]}]},{"name":"Petronilla","type":"FIRST","meanings":["An old female name; an Italian diminutive formed from Pietro, i.e. Peter."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Countess Petronilla de la Rivière was born in 1034, in Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italy. She had at least 1 daughter with Count Bernard Pierre of Terrasson. She died in 1085, in France, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1034–1085":"1034–1085","1025–1085":"1025–1085","1055–1103":"1055–1103","1103":"1103","1025":"1025","1034":"1034","1055":"1055","1085":"1085","Maguelone, , Bouches Du Rhine, France":"Prantsusmaa","Maguelone, Bouches Du Rhine, France":"Prantsusmaa","Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italy":"Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Itaalia","Terrasson, Dordogne, Aquitaine, France":"Terrasson, Dordogne, Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1034–1085":"1034–1085","1025–1085":"1025–1085","1055–1103":"1055–1103","1103":"1103","1025":"1025","1034":"1034","1055":"1055","1085":"1085","Maguelone, , Bouches Du Rhine, France":"Ranska","Maguelone, Bouches Du Rhine, France":"Ranska","Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italy":"Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italia","Terrasson, Dordogne, Aquitaine, France":"Terrasson, Dordogne, Aquitaine, Ranska"},"fr":{"1034–1085":"1034–1085","1025–1085":"1025–1085","1055–1103":"1055–1103","1103":"1103","1025":"1025","1034":"1034","1055":"1055","1085":"1085","Maguelone, , Bouches Du Rhine, France":"France","Maguelone, Bouches Du Rhine, France":"France","Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italy":"Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italie","Terrasson, Dordogne, Aquitaine, France":"Terrasson, Dordogne, Aquitaine, France","lifeSummary":"Countess Petronilla de la Rivière est née en 1034, à Terracina, Latina, Lazio, Italie. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Count Bernard Pierre of Terrasson. Elle est décédée en 1085, à France, à l’âge de 51 ans."},"de":{"1034–1085":"1034–1085","1025–1085":"1025–1085","1055–1103":"1055–1103","1103":"1103","1025":"1025","1034":"1034","1055":"1055","1085":